🧹 21. Cleanup & Maintenance

find /home -type f -mtime +90 -exec echo rm {} \;
find /home -type f -mtime +90 -exec rm {} \;

Or advanced way:

find /home -type f -mtime +90 \
  ! -path "/home/*/.*" \
  \( -name "*.log" -o -name "*.tmp" -o -name "*.cache" \) \
  -exec echo rm {} \;

It searches for old, non-hidden temporary files in /home and simulates deleting them.

find /home → search inside /home
-type f → only files (not directories)
-mtime +90 → files older than 90 days
! -path "/home/*/.*" → exclude hidden files (like .bashrc, .ssh)
\( -name "*.log" -o -name "*.tmp" -o -name "*.cache" \) → only logs, temp, and cache files
-exec echo rm {} \; → print delete commands instead of executing them



